HEADWORD: Nonconformist
<hw>Non`con*form"ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who does not conform
to an established church; especially, one who does not conform to the
established church of England; a dissenter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nonconformity</ent>⟦br⟧
